Read `/AGENTS.md` and `/docs/README.md` before every task.

The mandatory rules in AGENTS.md §4 are non-negotiable. If a task conflicts with them, stop and report the conflict.

## Key invariants
- Enrolment is created only when `Application.status = Admitted`.
- An Application may have multiple Payment attempts; each Payment belongs to the Application through `application_id NOT NULL`.
- A published or otherwise locked CourseVersion is immutable. Changes require Version N+1.
- Finance users cannot access DocumentSubmission data, metadata or signed document URLs.
- All state transitions go through approved state-machine classes, never raw status updates.
- Every sensitive state change and administrative override writes an atomic audit record.
- Browser payment callbacks are never trusted as final payment confirmation.
- Webhook and worker handlers must be idempotent.

## Document authority
- PRD governs scope and business intent.
- SRS governs functional behaviour, business rules and state machines.
- Technical Architecture governs implementation and coding standards.
- High-fidelity designs govern approved visual and interaction treatment.
- Screen Inventory governs coverage.
- Low-fidelity wireframes are supplementary.

If documents conflict, stop and identify the conflicting sections. Do not resolve the conflict by assumption.

## Documentation locations
- Product requirements: `/docs/product/`
- Design, inventory and wireframes: `/docs/design/`
- High-fidelity UX: `/docs/design/high-fidelity/`
- Technical architecture: `/docs/technical/`
- Decisions: `/docs/product/DECISION_LOG.md`

## Before editing
- Read the relevant SRS sections, technical standards and UX files.
- Inspect existing implementation patterns.
- For changes affecting more than 3 files, a migration, permissions, payments, state machines or sensitive data, present an implementation plan and wait for approval.
- Work only within the assigned work-package scope.

## Before completion (Work-Package Report)
When finishing a task, output a summary using this exact format:

**Title:** [Task Name]
**Files changed:** [List of files]
**Database migrations:** [Yes/No - list them if Yes]
**Permissions affected:** [List or "None"]
**State transitions affected:** [List or "None"]
**Tests added:** [List or "None"]
**Commands run:** [e.g., `composer install`, `phpunit`]
**Assumptions made:** [List or "None"]
**Known limitations / Blockers:** [List or "None"]

Do not claim completion if required tests were not run or did not pass.
